Content:
I dislike classes but I like bundling data along with methods which operate on that data.  I often find that JavaScript's classless objects are a great solution.  It's just so natural to be able to create an object with object literal syntax without first creating an ad hoc class and then instantiating it:<p><pre><code>  var o = {
      name: 'David',
      greet: function () {
          console.log('Hi, I am ' + this.name);
      }
  };</code></pre>
